text.text:
Stayed at Hotel Imperial Classic for one night, and it was far from what’s portrayed online. The images and descriptions are quite misleading, and we encountered several unpleasant surprises upon arrival.

We had booked a room for 3 people with two double beds, but were told we’d only get one double bed and a floor mattress instead. Definitely not what we paid for.

The room was small, poorly maintained, and had visible signs of dampness with paint peeling off. There were even tobacco and paan stains on the walls — quite unhygienic. Basic amenities like a water bottle, electric kettle, or tea/coffee weren’t provided either, which is expected at this price point.

The biggest letdown was the so-called “breakfast included”. We were handed a coupon and sent to a nearby roadside stall. While the food there was actually tasty, it was clearly not worth the ₹300 per person we were charged — especially when the same food costs ₹30 if bought directly.

Overall, this stay was a letdown — poor value for money, misleading advertising, and lack of basic hospitality. Would not recommend or return.

A 5-Star Resort… for Cockroaches

Ah, what can I say — truly an unforgettable stay! If you’re a fan of wildlife documentaries, this place is a hidden gem. I had the unique pleasure of sharing my room with a thriving colony of cockroaches, who clearly considered me the intruder.

Every night was an adventure: I came back hoping for rest and relaxation, but instead got to live out my own episode of Fear Factor, battling bugs until 4 a.m. Spoiler alert: they won. Even with daily anti-cockroach spray, they were so resilient I’m convinced they were wearing hazmat suits.

The shower didn’t work, which was just perfect — nothing like hauling water in a bucket to make you appreciate the finer things in life.
The room was never cleaned, but who needs that when you're already hosting an insect rave?

Oh, and the smell — somewhere between moldy basement and wet flip-flop. A true sensory experience.

Honestly, if you’re looking to bond with nature (very, very closely) and test your immune system, this is the place for you.

10/10. Would recommend to my worst enemy.

*Disappointing Experience at Hotel Sitara Paradise, Ameerpet*

I recently had the misfortune of staying at Hotel Sitara Paradise in Ameerpet, and I would strongly advise against it. Despite the online price range of ₹1800-₹2300, the front office staff refused to allow a 12:00 AM check-in, instead insisting on a direct booking for ₹2700/- for 24 hours.

The hotel's policy of not providing a 24-hour check-in and check-out facility is misleading, and the staff's behavior was unprofessional. The only redeeming quality was the breakfast, which was sourced from another hotel.

The AC room I booked had a non-functional AC, and the blanket provided was dirty, smelly, and infested with paddy bugs. The hotel's security was also a concern, as I witnessed staff and outsiders drinking in the reception hall late at night, making me and my wife feel uncomfortable and insecure.

Most of the rooms seemed to be designed like mini bars, which was not what I expected. Overall, my experience at Hotel Sitara Paradise was extremely disappointing, and I would not recommend it to anyone, especially families.

For Indian standards this is a great place and it was one of the reasonably priced hotels.

The bedroom was clean but had some questionable sheets with tiny stains.

Disappointing Stay – Not Worth the Price

I had high hopes for this hotel, but unfortunately, my experience was far from pleasant. The room was not clean — there were stains on the bedsheets and the bathroom smelled musty. The air conditioning barely worked, and the noise from the hallway kept me up at night.

To make matters worse, the staff seemed uninterested and unhelpful. When I raised concerns, they were either ignored or brushed off with vague promises that things would be "looked into."

For the price I paid, I expected a much better level of service and comfort. I won't be returning and wouldn't recommend this hotel to anyone.

I rarely write negative reviews, but this stay was frustrating from start to finish. First, the check-in process was a nightmare — we had to wait almost an hour because the front desk was understaffed and disorganized. When we finally got our room, it was nothing like the photos online. It looked old, poorly maintained, and honestly, dirty.

The bathroom had mold in the corners, the towels were stained, and the water pressure in the shower was pathetic. The bed was uncomfortable, the pillows smelled musty, and the sheets looked like they hadn't been changed. There were also insects in the room — we spotted a few cockroaches, which was absolutely disgusting.

What made it worse was the attitude of the staff. They were rude and dismissive when we raised our concerns. Housekeeping was impossible to reach, and even when they finally came, they barely cleaned anything. The "free Wi-Fi" barely worked, and the so-called "complimentary breakfast" was a joke — cold, tasteless food and dirty cutlery.

I felt completely let down and cheated. For the price we paid, I expected at least basic hygiene and decent service, but this hotel failed miserably on both counts. Avoid this place at all costs — there are far better options for the same or even lower price.

నేను సాధారణంగా నెగటివ్ రివ్యూలు రాయను, కానీ ఈ హోటల్‌లో నా అనుభవం పూర్తి నిరాశతో కూడినది. మొదటి నుంచే సమస్యలు మొదలయ్యాయి — చెక్ ఇన్ చేయడానికి గంటకు పైగా ఆగాల్సి వచ్చింది, స్టాఫ్ తగినంత మందిలో లేకపోవడం, పనిముట్టు లేని విధంగా వ్యవహరించడం స్పష్టంగా కనిపించింది.

గదిలోకి వెళ్ళాక అది ఫోటోలో చూపించినట్లుగా అస్సలు లేదు. పాతదిగా ఉంది, సరిగ్గా నిర్వహించలేదు, పైగా చాలా అస్వచ్ఛంగా అనిపించింది. బాత్రూమ్‌లో మూలలలో ప్లావు ఉంది, టవల్స్ మురికి మరకలతో ఉన్నాయి, షవర్ వాటర్ ప్రెషర్ చాలా తక్కువ. బెడ్ హార్డ్‌గా ఉంది, తలగడలు చీకటి వాసన వస్తున్నాయి, షీట్‌లు కూడా బాగాలేదనిపించింది.

ఇంకా దారుణం ఏంటంటే, స్టాఫ్ వ్యవహారం. వాళ్లకి ఫీడ్‌బ్యాక్ చెప్పినా స్పందన లేదు, ఉడుకుగా సమాధానం ఇచ్చారు. హౌస్‌కీపింగ్‌ను సంప్రదించడం చాలా కష్టమైంది, వచ్చినా సరే సరిగా క్లీన్ చేయలేదు. ఫ్రీ Wi-Fi ఉందంటారు కానీ కనెక్ట్ అవ్వదు. కంప్లిమెంటరీ బ్రేక్‌ఫాస్ట్ అంటారు కానీ చల్లటి, రుచి లేని భోజనం, పైగా ప్లేట్లు కూడా శుభ్రంగా లేవు.

ఈ హోటల్‌కి చెల్లించిన డబ్బుకి దీని స్థాయి అస్సలు సరిపోదు. ప్రాథమిక పారిశుద్ధ్యం కూడా లేకపోవడం బాధాకరం. ఎవరికీ ఈ హోటల్‌ని సిఫారసు చేయను. ఇదే ధరలో ఇంకా బాగా ఉన్న హోటల్స్ చాలా ఉన్నాయి.
అతిథిని అవమానంగా భావించే హోటల్ – చాలా దారుణమైన అనుభవం
ఈ హోటల్ గురించి రివ్యూలు చూసి బుక్ చేశాను, కానీ నేను పడిన అనుభవం చెప్పడానికి మాటలు లేవు. ఇది విశ్రాంతికి బదులు నరక యాతనగా మారింది.
చెక్-ఇన్ కి వచ్చిన వెంటనే అసౌకర్యాలు మొదలయ్యాయి. రిసెప్షన్ వద్ద స్టాఫ్ అసలు ఆతిథ్య భావనతో వ్యవహరించలేదు. ముఖంలో చిరునవ్వు లేకుండా, ఉదాసీనంగా మాట్లాడారు. రూమ్ ఇచ్చే సమయంలో కూడా అసౌకర్యంగా అనిపించింది — అడ్వాన్స్ గా బుక్ చేసుకున్నా కూడా ఖాళీ గది కోసం వేచి ఉండాల్సి వచ్చింది.

Rooms - Rooms are decent.

CONS:
1. Rooms Service - They dont provide any room service. They didn't cleaned our room during our 2 days stay.
2. By paying extra amount I booked a room with complimentary breakfast. But No Complimentary Breakfast will be given. If you ask anything like hot water , tea or coffee nothing will be given. Always Hotel manager will say Restaurant not opened.
3.Hygiene - No Soaps will be provided in Bathrooms.  If you book a Rs.500/- room through OYO they will provide new soaps and shampoos. But this hotel didn't provide anything. Bathroom cleanliness is not good.
4. TV didn't work in our room .
5.I feel Pricing of the rooms are much higher when you compare the services they are providing. For Less price You can get very good hotels with good service nearby Nampally Metro Station.
